OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1773162681
OL,3,CHorse dies at Cheltenham Festival
OL,4,Cafter sustaining 'fatal injury' in
OL,5,Csecond race
OL,7,FA statement from Cheltenham Racecourse
OL,8,Fregarding Hansard said: "While running
OL,9,Fon the flat in the second race of the
OL,10,Fday, Hansard sustained a fatal injury.
OL,12,F"He was quickly dismounted and
OL,13,Fimmediately attended to by a team of
OL,14,Fexpert veterinary professionals.
OL,16,F"In their assessment, it was concluded
OL,17,Fthat the best course of action for the
OL,18,Fhorse's welfare was for him to be put
OL,19,Fdown and our heartfelt condolences are
OL,20,Fwith his connections."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/2
